<H5>  Political Reform and the Hosokawa Cabinet's Responsibility </H5>
  During a news conference immediately after his inauguration, 
Prime Minister Hosokawa said: "I will take responsibility if I 
fail to enact the political reform bills during the ongoing Diet 
session." But the voters are not strict about Hosokawa's 
responsibility for the political reform issue. In our survey, 
only 21 percent said "the cabinet should resign en masse to take 
responsibility." On the other hand, 26 percent said "the 
cabinet should dissolve the lower house, and 38 percent said 
"neither the cabinet's resignation nor the lower house's 
dissolution is needed." 


