<H5>  Voters' Favorite Parties </H5>
  Following last month, the JNP again defended its number two 
position, beating the SDPJ. Until January 1992, more than 50 
percent of the voters said they would vote for the LDP, but the 
rate declined by half. 
NOTE: The survey, conducted by Chuo Research Inc. on 11-14 
November, was carried on as individual interviews of 2,000 
eligible voters picked at random. Responses were obtained from 
70.5 percent of, or 1,410, pollees. Data belong to the 
Multipurpose Statistic Databank of Tsukuba University. 

