<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Envoy Cited on Development of Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3112061293 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 0446 GMT 31 Dec 
93 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3112061293 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, December 30 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Ambassador of the PRC to Mongolia Pei Jiayi said in an interview 
to the MONTSAME correspondent that 1993 was the year of further 
normal development of relations between China and Mongolia in 
the direction of strengthening of good-neighbourly friendship 
and cooperation. 
  Parliaments, governments, some army organs and public 
organizations of the two countries have achieved expansion of 
friendly exchange, extension of mutual understanding and mutual 
confidence, stregthening of friendship, development of 
cooperation. In 1993 the number of trade points has increased, 
and that of the opened points has reached 11. The border trade 
is developing on a large scale as never before. According to 
the present data, 103 joint enterprises of China and Mongolia 
are registered in Mongolia. 
  Relations between the two countries, said the ambassador, 
have wide perspectives for development, as China and Mongolia as 
the neighbouring countries are pursuing a friendly policy of 
good-neighbourliness. The peoples of the two countries have 
traditional friendship, the two states are developing trade 
relations, having many years history. And plus mutual 
supplement of economy of the two countries. 
  Pei Jiayi expressed confidence that owing to mutual efforts 
relations of good-neighbourly friendly cooperation between the 
two countries will develop and strengthen from day to day 
continuously, being based on five principles of peaceful 
coexistence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

