<H3> <TI>   Tanzania-Korea Friendship Association Formed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0701045794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0418 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0701045794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 7 (KCNA) -- An inaugural meeting 
of the Tanzania-Korea Friendship Association was held in Dar es 
Salaam, Tanzania, on December 29. 
  Joseph Mbwiliza, vice-minister for water, energy and mineral 
resources and member of the National Executive Committee of the 
Revolutionary Party of Tanzania, was elected chairman of the 
Tanzania-Korea Friendship Association. 
  The chairman of the association in his speech said the 
association would briskly study and disseminate the chuche idea 
founded by the great leader President Kim Il-song, actively 
introduce and propagandize policies of the Workers' Party of 
Korea and the DPRK Government and lift up voices of support and 
solidarity for the cause of independent, peaceful reunification 
of Korea, the cherished national desire of the Korean people. 
  Letters to the great leader President Kim Il-song and the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il were adopted at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

