<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Postal Ministry To Cut Savings Rates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0701103194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0948 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0701103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 7 KYODO -- The Posts and 
Telecommunications Ministry announced Friday [7 January] that it 
will lower interest rates on some fixed-amount savings and time 
savings by 0.05 percentage point, effective Monday. 
  The rate on fixed-amount savings of less than six months 
will 
be kept unchanged at 1.22 percent per year while those on 
savings accounts of three years or more will be cut from the 
present 2.05 percent to 2.00 percent, ministry officials said. 
  The rate on time savings with a deposit period of three 
years 
will be reduced from 2.10 percent to 2.05 percent. 

</TEXT>

