<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Building of Population Centers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0601203394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1904 GMT 6 Jan 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0601203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 6 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Minister of Construction and Town-Building Ts. Damiran in an 
interview with the newspaper "ARDIYN ERH" correspondent 
announces that under conditions of the country's transiting to 
market relations also a system of settlement, population service 
and supply should be renewed. In T. Damiran's view, regioning 
of the country's territory, optimum location of the main centres 
of regions with corresponding infrastructure acquires now 
special importance. He notes that a priority development of the 
basic centers of regions will enable to organize properly the 
population service in different spheres of economy and culture, 
reduce a tendency for overcentralization of citizens in the 
capital. 
  T. Damiran considers that an advantage of regional 
development is more wide opportunities for cooperation of aymags 
in use of raw materials, natural wealth and labour resources, in 
use of pastures, in creation of conditions for the population 
for free living in different regions. 
  As T. Damiran notes, foundation of the main regional centers 
will enable to combine rationally nomadic and settled way of 
life of the population, ensure a balanced development of 
regions, rationally organize the ture [as received] and 
environment protection, develop tourism. 

</TEXT>

