<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Main Points of Draft `Action Program' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1001133394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1310 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1001133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 10 KYODO -- Following are the main 
points of a draft action program on improving access to Japan's 
construction market for foreigners obtained Monday [10 January] 
by KYODO NEWS SERVICE: 
  -- Transparency and competitiveness in bidding for public 
works projects should be boosted. The principle of 
nondiscrimination against foreigners should be implemented 
thoroughly. 
  -- Steps specified in the action program will be carried out 
starting in fiscal 1994, which begins on April 1. 
  -- Public works projects valued at more than specified sums 
should be put to open bidding. 
  -- Documents on bidding should be published in English as 
well as in Japanese. 
  -- New guidelines on bidding for public works will be 
drafted 
by around this summer. 

</TEXT>

