<H3> <TI>   Spanish Foreign Minister To Visit 14-16 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1001074894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0712 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1001074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 10 KYODO -- Spanish Foreign Minister 
Javier Solana Madariaga will visit Japan from Friday to Sunday 
on the first leg of an Asian tour that will also take him to 
South Korea, Thailand and Malaysia, Foreign Ministry officials 
said Monday [8 January]. 
  Solana, 51, will hold talks with his Japanese counterpart 
Tsutomu Hata on developments in Europe and the Asia-Pacific 
region, the officials said. 
  He will leave for South Korea on Sunday. 

