Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Naha, Jan. 10 KYODO -- A small wooden boat carrying 
21 people believed to be Vietnamese was spotted Sunday [9 
December] afternoon by a Japanese fishing vessel some 84 
kilometers southwest of Cape Kiyan in Itoman on Okinawa Island, 
local maritime officials said. 
  A Maritime Safety Agency patrol boat confirmed the same day 
that the five-ton craft, adrift in international waters in the 
East China Sea, is carrying 21 people, including women. 
  A patrol boat will inspect the boat when it enters Japanese 
territorial waters, the officials said. 
  It was the first time this year a boat reportedly carrying 
refugees was spotted in the vicinity of Okinawa, they said. 

