<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA-DPRK Talks on Nuclear Issue Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   1st Contact `Very Productive' </H4>
<F P=102> SK0701231094 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2200 GMT 7 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0701231094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Cha Man-sun from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] The International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] held 
the first official contact with North Korea in Vienna, Austria, 
this morning and discussed the issue of resuming the inspections 
of the seven nuclear facilities North Korea had reported to the 
IAEA but a conclusion has not been reached. 
  The three North Korean representatives, including Yun 
Ho-chin, counselor of the North Korean Embassy in Vienna, 
visited the IAEA at 0000 this morning, Korean time, and 
delivered North Korea's official message containing its will 
[uisa] to accept overall inspections [chonmyon sachal]. Then, 
the North Korean representatives held the first official 
working-level contact with (Belcos), director of the IAEA 
Inspection Department, and negotiated working-level problems 
regarding the resumption of inspections of the reported seven 
nuclear facilities for two hours. 
  After the working-level negotiations, North Korean 
representatives revealed in an interview with KBS that even 
though the two sides have failed to reach an agreement, they 
held very productive negotiations. 
  Counselor Yun Ho-chin, North Korea's representative, said 
that during the official contact the two sides discussed their 
opinions regarding the resumption of inspections and shared 
opinions to settle the points at issue through negotiations so 
that inspections may be smoothly conducted. He said they agreed 
to meet once again early next week. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

