<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA-DPRK Talks on Nuclear Issue Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   2d Official Working-Level Contact Held </H4>
<F P=102> SK1001123494 Seoul YONHAP in English 1201 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1001123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, Jan. 10 (YONHAP) -- North Korea and the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) on Monday morning 
(local time) opened the second official working-level contact on 
matters related to IAEA inspection of North Korean nuclear 
facilities. 
  IAEA spokesman Hans Meyer said that at the meeting, the IAEA 
produced to North Korea technical requirements related to 
nuclear inspections. 
  Meyer said the contact was going on between the two sides, 
and he could not discuss any details. 
  He added, however, he expects additional talks could take 
place this week on the inspection of the seven declared North 
Korean nuclear facilities. 
  Another IAEA spokesman, David Kyd, said he doesn't believe 
there would be any immediate progress over the question of 
inspecting two undeclared facilities. 
  North Korea was represented at the second contact held at 
the 
IAEA headquarters here in Vienna by Yun Ho-chin, a councilor at 
the North Korean embassy in Vienna, and a couple of other 
diplomats. 

</TEXT>

