<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   SLORC To Hold Talks With Rebel Groups </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0901105794 Rangoon Burma Television Network in Burmese 
1330 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0901105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Burma Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Excerpts" of Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt's address </F>
delivered at city hall in Loikaw, Kayah State during his visit 
on 8 Jan] 
  [Excerpts] Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt, chairman of the 
Work Committee for Development of Border Areas and National 
Races and secretary-1 of the State Law and Order Restoration 
Council [SLORC], accompanied by Lt. Gen. Maung Thint, minister 
of development of border areas and national races; Brigadier 
General Myo Thant, minister of information; Colonel Pe Thein, 
minister of education; U Khin Maung Thein, minister of energy; 
construction minister, director generals and managing directors 
from the respective departments and enterprises, and responsible 
personnel left Yangon [Rangoon] on a defense services plane this 
morning. They arrived at Loikaw Airport in Kayah State at 0900 
in the morning. [passage omitted] 
  In his address Lt. Gen. Khin Nyunt said that a delegation 
led 
by him visited Loikaw last September [month as heard], and 
during the meeting with town residents, native village leaders, 
and departmental personnel, the SLORC invited the jungle-based 
armed organizations to return to the legal fold so as to meet, 
coordinate, and to hold discussions for the reunification of 
national brethren. [passage omitted] 
  He added that Myanmar [Burma] is a union which comprises 
various indigenous nationals who reside together. Moreover, in 
Myanmar the indigenous nationals have been residing unitedly in 
the union through weal and woe for more than 1,000 years, and it 
is a country with its own culture. The colonialist-imperialists 
coveted the country's prosperity, and the abundant natural 
resources, staging three wars of aggression and enslaving 
Myanmar. [Passage omitted]. Although it has been over 40 years 
since independence, regions with the rule of law and tranquility 
have been developed to a certain extent, while regions infested 
with insurgency are still lagging behind. 
  He added that The SLORC's objectives are: the brethren who 
are indigenous nationals in the union must develop evenly, and 
all indigenous nationals must have a right to enjoy the taste of 
independence, which is achieved by all indigenous nationals 
joining hands and working unitedly. It is realized that 
national reconciliation is crucial in the implementation of 
these objectives. That is why, jungle-based armed organizations 
are invited to return to the legal fold. The state government 
has been extending this invitation with genuine goodwill and is 
intent on working for the consistent development of all states, 
including the border areas; allowing all the indigenous 
nationals to enjoy the taste of independence; and seeking the 
rapid development of the whole union. 
  He said that due to the invitation, the SLORC will meet and 
coordinate with some jungle-based armed organizations in the 
near future. The light of hope for peace is emerging. Every 
one has to continue to work for the full-fledged emergence of 
this light of hope for peace. In the upcoming meeting, the 
SLORC will participate with complete sincerity, and honesty. He 
added that, while people are needed to support this meeting 
actively and unitedly, the jungle-based armed organizations are 
also required to hold discussions with genuine goodwill and an 
honest attitude. These objectives will be accomplished for sure 
if both parties base their discussions on honesty, and loyalty. 
He also said that the cabinet ministers are accompanying him to 
accelerate development activities in Kayah State if it becomes 
peaceful and tranquil. 
  He said the light of peace is beginning to emerge in Kayah 
State and the SLORC is ready to implement rapid regional 
development in Kayah State once the region becomes stable and 
tranquil. The SLORC is simply explaining and presenting the 
state government's genuine attitude and intention to all the 
indigenous nationals. That is why all people, regardless of 
their race and religion, and all indigenous nationals who are 
residing in the Kayah State are needed to work together for the 
success of SLORC's objectives and aims. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

