<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Contingent Leaves for Somalia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0801065594 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0428 GMT 8 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0801065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, 8 Jan. (OANA-BERNAMA) -- The first 
batch of 450 men of the Seventh Battalion of the Royal Rangers 
Regiment (RARD) left here Saturday morning for a six-month tour 
of duty under the United Nations Operations in Somalia (UNOSOM). 
  The men, in full combat gear, were seen off by Army Chief 
Gen. Borhan Ahmad and other army top brass. 
  Their families were also at the Royal Malaysian Air Force 
Base in Subang near here to bid them farewell. The 
Mentakab-based rangers will form the Malaysian Battalion 
(Malbatt) II in Mogadishu, relieving Malbatt I which comprises 
mainly members of the mechanised 19th Royal Malay Regiment 
(RAMD) based in Sungai Petani. 
  While the members of the 19th RAMD are returning, the 
rangers 
are being sent to the Horn of Africa in Batcheas from today. 
The next flight on the UN-chartered civil aircraft will be on 
Jan. 10. 

</TEXT>

