<H3> <TI>   Government Delegation's PRC Agenda Reviewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1001071994 Phnom Penh National Voice of Cambodia Radio 
Network in Cambodian 0430 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1001071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Voice of Cambodia Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A government official has disclosed that the heads 
of the royal government of the Kingdom of Cambodia [KOC], Prince 
Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh, first prime minister; and Hun Sen, 
KOC second prime minister; and a number of ministers, state 
secretaries, under state secretaries, and leading officials will 
pay an official visit to the PRC from 17 January. 
  This trip by the two heads of the royal government of 
Cambodia [RGC] is made at the invitation of His Excellency 
[H.E.] Li Peng, PRC prime minister. It is also their first 
joint visit since the official establishment of the royal 
government on 29 September 1993. 
  It ought to be specified that during this trip to China, the 
two RGC heads will probably inform King Norodom Sihanouk, who is 
receiving medical treatment in Beijing, of the royal 
government's major plans, projects, and principles for 1994. 
  Political analysts on the Cambodia issue have affirmed that 
during this visit to Beijing by the two RGC heads -- made after 
the attack by Khmer Rouge troops on Romchang village in the 
liberated zone of FUNCINPEC [National United Front for an 
Independent, Neutral, Peaceful, and Cooperative Cambodia] on 1 
January -- discussion and consultation with the king will 
probably be held concerning the Khmer Rouge, who also want a 
role in the royal government, because China in the past was a 
major supporter of the Khmer Rouge. 

</TEXT>

