<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chea Sim Asks For Armed Forces Unity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0901102794 Phnom Penh National Voice of Cambodia Radio 
Network in Cambodian 0430 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0901102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Voice of Cambodia Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday [8 January], Samdech Chea Sim, acting 
head of state and chairman of the National Assembly, visited 
troops of the Khmer Royal Armed Forces [KRAF] in Division 1 in 
the Kirirom area and also visited the area's major tourist 
sites. Accompanying him on this trip were His Excellency 
General Tie Banh, co-defense minister; princes; excellencies; 
and many officials from the National Defense Ministry. 
  Speaking on this occasion, Samdech Chea Sim most cordially 
and warmly enquired about life in the KRAF's Division 1, which 
is stationed in Kirirom. He further said that there are two 
tasks for Division 1: first, defend the Kirirom area and protect 
the local natural resources; and second, build bridges and roads 
coming into Kirirom. Samdech Chea Sim also called on the 
officers and men in charge of the entire area to continue 
further heightening their spirit of responsibility in the 
protection of the area's natural resources as well as in the 
speedy and timely construction of roads and bridges leading to 
the Kirirom area. He also appealed to Division 1 to strengthen 
and expand national unity with forces from all political parties 
in order to become the KRAF under the direct leadership of the 
Royal Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  Samdech Chea Sim also distributed some gifts in the form of 
foodstuff to officers and men stationed in the Kirirom area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

