<H3> <TI>   French Flights to Siem Reap, Ho Chi Minh City Begin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0801125294 Phnom Penh AKP in English 1003 GMT 8 Jan 93 </F>
<F P=103> BK0801125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP January 8 -- A French aircraft began 
regular commercial flights on Friday following an inauguration 
ceremony at the international airport of Pochentong. 
  The commencement of flight by the French plane of A.T.R. 72, 
chartered by the Cambodian Aviation Company at a monthly cost of 
238,000 U.S. dollars, is made in accordance with an agreement 
signed recently in Phnom Penh by the officials of the aviation 
companies of the two countries, Mr. Tep Hen and Daniel Tomasi. 
  The 70-seat A.T.R. 72 will perform regular local flight from 
Phnom Penh to the town of Siem Reap where the famous temples of 
Angkor Wat is located and the other flight from Phnom Penh to Ho 
Chi Minh City (Vietnam), said Tep Hen. 

</TEXT>

