<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Bars All Visits With Timor Rebel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0801123694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0801123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Indonesian Government has temporarily barred 
anyone from visiting East Timor rebel leader Xanana Gusmao in 
prison. The indefinite decision also applies to his relatives 
and officials of the International Committee of the Red Cross 
[ICRC]. Baharuddin Lopa, director general for corrections of 
the Justice Department, told reporters in Jakarta this afternoon 
that the decision was made because Xanana had discredited 
Indonesia's reputation in the international community by sending 
a letter to the Portuguese Government and the International 
Commission of Justice. 
  Baharuddin Lopa said the Indonesian Government was generous 
enough to allow Xanana's family and ICRC officials to see him 
without the presence of any Indonesian official. Xanana, 
however, had abused the generosity by smuggling out the letter. 
  According to Baharuddin Lopa, an agreement will 
automatically 
become null and void if either party violates it under 
international law. In the wake of the incident, the director 
general for corrections has instructed his subordinates to 
closely guard Xanana in case the rebel leader is again allowed 
to receive visitors. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-47112 </DOCNO>
