<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing-Led PRC Military Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<H4>   Supreme Commander on Weapons Purchase </H4>
<F P=102> BK0901132394 Bangkok ZHONG HUA RIBAO in Chinese 8 Jan 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> BK0901132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok ZHONG HUA RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Liu Huaqing, vice chairman of the Chinese 
Central Military Commission, paid a courtesy call on Supreme 
Commander Air Chief Marshal [ACM] Woranat Aphichari at the 
Supreme Command Headquarters yesterday. The two sides also held 
cordial talks. 
  After the meeting, ACM Woranat briefed correspondents on the 
results of his talks with Liu Huaqing. He said that Liu Huaqing 
had told him that China is willing to sell weapons to Thailand. 
On this issue, ACM Woranat told the Chinese side that the Thai 
military units have to stick to their plans when it comes to 
procuring any weapons and cannot buy weapons at will. Warships 
ordered by the Navy are now under construction in China. 
  ACM Woranat also said that Thailand has no policy of setting 
up refugee holding centers along the border. Any rumors 
regarding such a matter are untrue. 

</TEXT>

