<F P=103> BK1001142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan 10 -- The Central Committee of the 
Communist Party of Vietnam has sent a message of condolences to 
its Lao counterpart on the demise of Phoumi Vongvichit, advisor 
to the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party 
(LPRP), former Politburo member of the LPRP Central Committee, 
and former acting president of Laos, former deputy prime 
minister and minister of education and former president of the 
Lao Front for National Construction. 
  "Comrade Phoumi Vongvichit is an outstanding leader of the 
Lao party and state, and a staunch fighter who strived much for 
national independence and the people's happiness. He was a 
close friend of the Vietnamese people and made many precious 
contributions to the consolidation and development of the 
special friendship and solidarity between the two countries", 
the message says. 

</TEXT>

