<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Issues Timber Export Order </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0801155094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0801155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 29 December 1993, the prime minister issued a 
decision on the exportation of timber and forestry products. The 
decision contains the following main points: 
  -- Timber products including raw (?and processed) timber and 
forestry products entitled to export must include complete 
products, which are processed in accordance with required 
technical standards. 
  -- The names, categories, shapes, and measurements of these 
products are defined in the list attached to this decision. 
  -- To export these products, exporters must provide the 
correct names of products, their unit quantities, nature, 
measurements, qualities, and unit prices. They must also 
provide pictures of products or product samples. As for those 
products with complex shapes, there must be descriptive color 
photographs. 
  -- All export contracts and attached photographs should be 
original ones with signatures and seals of the sellers and the 
signatures and seals, if any, of the buyers. 
  The decision also sets forth a number of measures to deal 
with the exportation of timber and forestry products other than 
those cited in the attached list. 

</TEXT>

