<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Communist Party Condemns Clinton's Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0801101094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1006 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0801101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 8 (KCNA) -- National Chairman of 
the Communist Party of the USA Gus Hall in an article published 
in the party's organ PEOPLE'S WEEKLY WORLD urged all the 
Americans to protest Clinton's policy threatening North Korea 
with a nuclear preemptive strike. 
  In an article calling for a nuclear-free world he pointed 
out 
that the current threat to world peace comes from the US policy 
of nuclear aggression against North Korea. 
  He noted that the United States is stepping up preparations 
for a nuclear preemptive strike at North Korea. 
  Direct nuclear threat to North Korea is part of the anti- 
communist and anti-socialist policy pursued continuously by the 
United States, he said, and added: It is the same policy as the 
nuclear business in the old cold-war era. 
  Facts show that Clinton is more bellicose than his 
predecessors, he stated. 
  He branded the U.S. imperialists as the very one actually 
threatening world peace. 
  He called upon the anti-war, anti-imperialist forces to 
rebuild America's peace movement to conduct activities with a 
demand for a stop to the threat to North Korea and demand for 
the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from South Korea. 

</TEXT>

