<F P=103> SK1001051294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Chinese Premier Favors Negotiated Solution of Nuclear </F>
Problem" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng at a talk with the Japanese foreign minister Saturday 
emphasized that the nuclear problem on the Korean peninsula 
would be resolved through negotiations, according to a XINHUA 
report. 
  Li said China supports the non-nuclear proposal and 
stability 
and peace there. 
  "We oppose any coercive way or embargo, which will 
inevitably 
make the problem more complicated," Li said. 

</TEXT>

