<F P=102>  SK0901235794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2120 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0901235794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2120 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Comrade Li Peng, premier of the PRC State Council, 
on 8 January held talks with the Japanese foreign minister and 
stressed the need to resolve the nuclear issue on the Korean 
peninsula through dialogue, according to XINHUA news agency. 
  Referring to the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula, he 
pointed out: China supports the stance of realizing the 
denuclearization on the Korean peninsula and maintaining 
security and peace on the peninsula. We hope that the nuclear 
issue will be resolved reasonably through dialogue. We do not 
approve of using means of imposing pressure or sanctions since 
such ways can bring an adverse effect and produce discrepancy on 
the issue. 

