<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam New Year's News Conference Condemned </TI></H3>
<H4>   Remarks in Papers Cited </H4>
<F P=102> SK0801104794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1041 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0801104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 8 (KCNA) -- Papers here today say 
the traitor Kim Yong-sam's "New Year press conference" proved 
again that the South Korean "civilian" regime is only a disguise 
and it is not different from the successive military fascist 
regimes and that there is nothing to be expected from it. 
  A NODONG SINMUN analyst says: 
  What he said at the press conference boils down to the 
praise 
of his "achievements" whereby he embellished his treacheries as 
patriotism with flowery words, the advertisement of "policy" 
without any concrete proposal and deceptive, infeasible 
"commitments." His self-praise was intended to defend his 
monstrous crimes against the country and the nation in the first 
year of office and avoid his responsibility for them. 
  Kim Yong-sam got on the nerve of the North, groundlessly 
charging it with the "nuclear problem." He cried for "military 
reform and modernization" and "security posture" to cope with 
possible "provocations" by the North. He obtrusively blared 
that they have the "final say" as regards the "Team Spirit" 
joint military exercises and the United States "respects" their 
will. 
  This year, too, he, far from showing his willingness for 
reunification, intends to seek North-South confrontation as he 
did in the first year of office marked by treacheries. He is 
really a traitor to the nation and a human dreg who deserves 
condemnation by the 70 million people of our nation. 
  Regarding the internal problems of South Korea, Kim Yong-sam 
cried for "continued progress of change and reform" and 
"internationalization of the whole society," as if he would do 
something in the second year of office. He, however, failed to 
put forward any concrete proposal. 
  His voluble eloquence at the hurriedly called press 
conference in the new year is the extension of the old game of 
the political prostitute to attain the "security of power" by 
quelling the protest of the people against such treacherous acts 
of the "civilian" regime as rice market opening and taking the 
edge off their anti- "government" struggle. 
  A MINJU CHOSON analyst says that whatever honeyed 
"commitments" the "civilian" traitor may make, while enriching 
outside forces and the privileged circles at the sacrifice of 
the people, no one will be deceived. 

</TEXT>

