<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `War Exercises' in South Said `Provocative' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0901083094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0808 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0901083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 9 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
puppets staged on January 6 and 7 provocative ground and air war 
exercises against the North in the vicinity of the Demilitarized 
Zone along the Military Demarcation Line [MDL], according to 
military sources. 
  In the war games in Paju, Yonchon, Inje, Kanghwa and Kimpo 
Counties ground attack units fired hundreds of large-calibre 
machinegun and automatic rifle bullets, charging towards the MDL. 
  And puppet Air Force units engaged themselves in a drill of 
support to ground attack units and intensive attack by missiles 
on targets in coastline areas of the Northern half of the 
country and a drill of intensive airlifting at night by large 
transport planes. 

</TEXT>

