<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Provincial Plenary Meetings View Economic Strategy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0801111594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1059 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0801111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 8 (KCNA) -- Plenary meetings of 
the provincial (municipal) committees of the Workers' Party of 
Korea were held recently. 
  The plenary meetings discussed tasks of implementing the 
resolution of the 21st plenary meeting of the Sixth Party 
Central Committee. 
  The plenary meeting of the party Central Committee held in 
December last year, on the basis of a deep analysis of the 
practical requirements of socialist construction in Korea, 
decided to set the next three years as a period for adjustment 
in socialist economic construction and put forth strategic 
agriculture first, light industry first and foreign trade first 
policies in this period. 
  The plenary meetings of the provincial (municipal) party 
committees stressed that the Korean people are now faced with an 
honorable task of stepping up socialist economic construction to 
further increase the might of the Korean-style socialism and 
bring its advantages into fuller play, while consolidating the 
achievements made in the implementation of the Third Seven-Year 
Plan. 
  They expressed the determination to implement the party's 
revolutionary economic strategy of directing primary efforts to 
agriculture, the light industry and foreign trade in the period 
of adjustment for socialist economic construction. 

</TEXT>

