<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tokyo Approves 1.57 Billion Yen for Cambodia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1101082794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0811 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1101082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 11 KYODO -- Japan will extend a total 
of 1.57 billion yen to Cambodia to help with projects to improve 
water supplies and sewage systems in Phnom Penh and to repair a 
road construction center, the Foreign Ministry said Tuesday [11 
January]. 
  The latest offering brings total Japanese aid to Cambodia 
for 
this fiscal year to 7.9 billion yen, the ministry said. 
  The assistance includes 98 million yen to repair and expand 
a 
water purification plant and construct conduit pipes, it said. 
  It also includes up to 59 million yen to purchase equipment 
to repair the road construction center, it said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

