<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Announces Aid to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1001122394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1202 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1001122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 10 KYODO -- Japan is to extend a total 
of 762 million yen to Rwanda for debt relief and to help ease 
its economic difficulties, Foreign Ministry officials said 
Monday [10 January]. 
  Officials of the two governments exchanged notes on the 
assistance in Nairobi, Kenya, they said. 
  The aid includes 461 million yen for a project to buy 
equipment to maintain national roads, and 300 million yen to 
promote economic structural reform efforts and to ease economic 
difficulties including debt problems. 
  Also included is 1.81 million yen to cover debts for which 
repayment fell due in the latter half of fiscal 1992, ended last 
March, but on which capital and rescheduled interest has not yet 
been paid, they said. 

</TEXT>

